title: Wrong data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set
description: When attempting to set a filter expression of 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set returns incorrect results or a null result set.
OB: When setting the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0', the data set returns incorrect results or an empty result set.
EB: The system should display a relevant error message when an invalid or unsupported filter expression is set.
SR:
1. Open the data set page.
2. Set the filter expression to 'row[0] equals to 0'.
3. Observe if the data set returns incorrect results or an empty result set.
4. Verify if a relevant error message is displayed when an invalid or unsupported filter expression is set.
